Liverpool have confirmed that their goalkeeper, Daniel Atherton has left the club to join Marine on loan until the end of the season. The UEFA Champions League holders made this known in a statement on their official website on Wednesday. The statement read: “Daniel Atherton has joined Marine on loan until the end of the season. “The Liverpool Academy goalkeeper will spend the rest of the 2019-20 campaign with the promotion-chasing Northern Premier League North West Division club. “Atherton, 20, is a member of the Reds’ U23s squad and made two appearances for the first team during pre-season in 2019.”